espace. Old index keys can\n   868\tremain as harmless derived metadata until a future pruning/rebuild mechanism is\n   869\tworth building.\n   870\t\n   871\tAdding indexes is not a large GitMeta model cost if they remain derived lookup\n   872\tkeys. The real costs are write amplification, stale-index rebuild behavior, key\n   873\texplosion, sync bloat, and making sure readers do not treat\n   874\t`agentlog-index:*` as durable association truth.\n   875\t\n   876\tFor a branch-name query, lookup can start from turns where that branch was\n   877\tobserved in the stack/branch snapshot, then boost turns where commits on that\n   878\tbranch matched files from a previous worktree snapshot.\n   879\t\n   880\tFor a PR/review-id query, lookup can start from turns where a branch carried\n   881\tthat review identifier, then optionally expand through the PR branch, head\n   882\tcommits, change ids, and touched paths.\n   883\t\n   884\tFor read-time association scoring:\n   885\t\n   886\t1. find candidate turns from branch, review, or change indexes\n   887\t2. verify candidates against `TurnDetail.observed_targets`\n   888\t3. count observed branches/stacks/review units\n   889\t4. compare previous-turn worktree files with current-turn committed files\n   890\t5. rank candidate sessions, turns, changes, branches, and PRs\n   891\t6. return derived confidence, reasons, and highlighted turn windows without\n   892\t   writing a durable relationship\n   893\t\n   894\t## V1 Decision Details\n   895\t\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T14:19:08.517Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}